ARTICLE.TITLE: Police chief vows to shut down illegal parties after second night of violence
ARTICLE.TEXT:
Officers regroup after being attacked by crowds in Notting Hill last night. Dame Cressida Dick said that 140 officers had been injured by members of the public in recent weeks

Britain’s most senior police officer today described attacks on police officers breaking up illegal parties as “utterly unacceptable”.

Dame Cressida Dick, the Metropolitan police commissioner, warned of the potential for further violence after officers were attacked for a second night in a row as they attempted to disperse crowds. She called on the public to report illegal events and vowed: “We will come and close them down.”

Meanwhile, Manchester police said that they had arrested a 32-year-old woman over a double killing at an outdoor party on Saturday. Abayomi Ajose, 36, was gunned down along with 21-year-old Cheriff Tall at a “spontaneous gathering” that followed a Black Lives Matter family event in Moss Side.
